# 3. この一瞬のためだけに

Shizuku: ...!
Second Years: Wow! Again, no misses! You're a total pro now, Asahina!
Mafuyu: I have you and the others to thank. Hehe. I never realized how good it'd feel when your arrow goes where you want it to.
Second Years: I know, right?! I think all of us remember the first time we hit the target.
Shizuku: (Asahina's so incredible... That means I also need to...!)
Shizuku: H-Huh? My arrow fell...
Archery Club Captain: Oh, you dropped your arrow. Don't worry. That happened to me a lot when I was first starting out.
Archery Club Captain: Try relaxing a bit. It tends to happen when you grip your draw hand a little too tightly.
Shizuku: O-Okay!
Shizuku: My draw hand... That's my right hand... Relax a bit and...
Shizuku: Oh no. It happened again...
First Years: Hey, I hit it!
First Years: Me too! It's my first ever!
Shizuku: (Oh... The other first years are starting to show signs of improvement...)
Archery Club Captain: Hehe. It's normal to feel a little anxious with the newcomer tournament coming up and all, but it's okay. These things happen when you're just starting to learn.
Archery Club Captain: I know you're also busy as an idol, Hinomori, so let's just take it one step at a time!
Shizuku: Okay...
Shizuku: What? You're changing agencies?
Airi: Yup! So, a lot happened and I put in my papers yesterday...
Shizuku: B-But why...?! As far as I could tell, things have been going very well for you recently.
Airi: Yeah... It was nice to hear that our viewers liked seeing me...
Airi: But it's not the kind of success I was looking for... As a result, I got into a big argument with my manager and the agency CEO...
Shizuku: What do you mean? Not the kind of success you were looking for...?
Airi: Oh, don't worry about that. I should be fine from here on out...!
Airi: I put a lot of thought into it and decided that I need to change agencies in order to succeed in the way I actually want. So, again, I'll be fine.
Shizuku: I see...
Shizuku: I still have some questions, but you have my support, Airi. I agree that you should do as your heart says...
Shizuku: However, it is sad to see you leave our agency...
Airi: Hehe. That makes us rivals now. Watch out cause I'm not pulling any punches!
Shizuku: Right... Let's both do our best.
???: ...zuku! Shizuku...!
Shizuku: Huh? Y-Yes! What is it?
Leader: You're the only one who still hasn't put on their outfit, right? Is everything okay? You seem preoccupied.
Shizuku: Uh, no! I'm okay!
Leader: Well, if you say so... The show's about to start, so I need to get going...
Shizuku: (What am I doing...?)
Shizuku: (I made the decision to do my best as an idol, at school and at club.)
Shizuku: (But I've been having so much trouble that I've needed to rely on others just to get by...)
Shizuku: (And worst of all... I couldn't see what Airi was going through...)
Shizuku: I need to do better...
Shizuku: For the sake of our fans, I need to be perfect. I have to do my absolute best...
Shizuku: Another miss...
Shizuku: (I've learned to actually shoot arrows, but I'm yet to hit the target...)
Shizuku: (At this rate, I won't be able to do anything meaningful during the newcomer tournament...)
Shizuku: (The other girls from my year are showing clear signs of improvement, while I...)
Shizuku: (It's only natural for a skill gap to develop since I can't attend every day...)
Shizuku: (But I'm also having trouble as an idol.)
Shizuku: (Nothing has been going well despite how hard I've been trying... I couldn't even help Airi...)
Shizuku: Wh-What am I doing...?
Shizuku: (I know it was recommended to me, but continuing with archery isn't a good idea...)
Shizuku: (In this state, I'm only going to become a burden to the other club members.)
Shizuku: (Once the tournament is over, I'll...)
???: Hm? Hinomori...?
Shizuku: Huh? A-Asahina...!
Mafuyu: Hello. Were you practicing by yourself?
Shizuku: Y-Yes. Are you here to do the same...?
Mafuyu: Yes, since we have that tournament coming up. I've been coming to practice in the morning for about a month now.
Mafuyu: Still, Hinomori, I'm impressed by how you've been balancing being both an idol and a member of this club.
Shizuku: No, you give me too much credit...
Shizuku: I've yet to hit the target even once, so I'd like to learn how to at least hit it before the tournament...
Mafuyu: Hehe. That's exactly why I'm so impressed by you.
Mafuyu: You're doing your very best to overcome the obstacle that's in front of you.
Shizuku: I am...?
Shizuku: (Yes, I suppose she's right...)
Shizuku: (But Asahina's been practicing when no one else is around...)
Shizuku: (Compared to me, she's much more...)
Mafuyu: Is something the matter, Hinomori...?
Shizuku: Oh, uh... N-No... It's just...
Shizuku: You're such an incredible person, Asahina...
Mafuyu: Huh?
Shizuku: You're such a good archer and a wonderful person... I am trying my best like you said, but I'm struggling to produce results.
Shizuku: Because of that... I've been causing everyone around me so much trouble.
Shizuku: Why...? Why can't I be more perfect like you, Asahina...?
Mafuyu: I'm not perfect...
Mafuyu: Far from it. That's why I'm here.
Shizuku: What?
Mafuyu: Taking up archery made me realize something. This place... It calms me.
Shizuku: It calms you...?
Mafuyu: Yes.
Mafuyu: I believe this is a place where you have no choice but to clear your mind of all other thoughts.
Mafuyu: If your mind wanders at all... If you're not fully focused on your arrow... It won't hit the target.
Mafuyu: So, I set everything aside when I'm here... School, my friends, all of it...
Mafuyu: Focusing only on shooting has this way of calming me...
Mafuyu: I have a feeling that you'll be able to move forward if you learn to do that...
Shizuku: (Set everything aside...and calm my mind...)
Shizuku: (Yes, she may be right...)
Shizuku: (I've been so focused on “being perfect” that I let it get to me.)
Shizuku: (I need to simplify things... I need to temporarily set all of my worries aside...)
Shizuku: (Then, I might just be able to move forward...)
Mafuyu: Would you like to join me, Hinomori? We can try attaining that calmness together.
Shizuku: Together...? Are you sure?
Mafuyu: Yes, of course. Let's try together.
Shizuku: Thank you, Asahina...
Shizuku: Okay, I'll give it a try...
Shizuku: (First, establish your stance. Correct your posture...)
Shizuku: (Nock your arrow. Grasp the string. Maintain your posture. Raise your bow and arms...)
Shizuku: (Stay focused. No mistakes...!)
Shizuku: ...
Shizuku: (I need to get it right...!)
Mafuyu: Don't worry, Hinomori.
Shizuku: What...?
Mafuyu: Take a deep breath. And focus on just that.
Mafuyu: This shot is all you care about right now.
Shizuku: This shot...
Shizuku: (Right. I can't let anything else into my head...)
Shizuku: (You don't need to be perfect. Just focus. Calm yourself...)
Shizuku: (This shot is all that matters right now. Focus only on that...!)
Shizuku: *Gasp*
Shizuku: I-It hit...! Asahina, my arrow hit...!
Mafuyu: Yes...! Congratulations, Hinomori!
Mafuyu: If you learn to repeat that, I'm sure you'll do just fine during the newcomer tournament.
Shizuku: ...
Shizuku: Thank you very much, Asahina. I'm... I'm overcome with joy...
Shizuku: I was so worried that nothing would go right for me... I really didn't know what to do...
Mafuyu: Hehe. You're a hardworking person, Hinomori, so I suspected that you were overthinking things a little.
Mafuyu: Whenever that happens, it can feel like the walls are closing in on you, and you hate everything...
Mafuyu: However, I think you'll be fine now that you've learned to calm your mind.
Mafuyu: I have a feeling that you'll be able to push much further ahead now.
Shizuku: Yes... So do I.
Shizuku: Again, Asahina, thank you very much!
